(1, 1, 'FED-TET-PE-01', 'TET Subject Mastery: Concepts to Competence', '4 weeks (12â€“15 hrs)', 'Strengthen subject knowledge & apply in TET scenarios', 'Blended (video lessons, live Q&A, practice drills, self-paced study)', 'The Teacher Eligibility Test (TET) is a gateway for aspiring educators to demonstrate subject mastery and teaching competency. Many educators face challenges not in knowing content, but in applying concepts in competency-based questions. This course provides a structured pathway to help educators reinforce subject fundamentals, avoid common mistakes, and confidently approach high-stakes TET questions.', 'Basic familiarity with TET syllabus (Math, EVS, Language, Pedagogy)\r\nâ€¢\r\nPrior classroom teaching or teacher training background (preferred, not mandatory)\r\nâ€¢\r\nAccess to digital learning tools (internet, laptop/smartphone)', 'Aspiring teachers preparing for CTET/TET exams\r\nâ€¢\r\nCurrent faculty & educators looking for refresher training in subject application\r\nâ€¢\r\nTeacher trainees in B.Ed./D.El.Ed. programs', 'This 4-week blended learning program equips educators with subject clarity and exam-oriented application strategies. The course covers Math, Environmental Studies, and Language through a structured roadmap, enabling participants to\r\ntransition from â€œconcept understandingâ€ to â€œquestion-solving competence.â€ Interactive drills, diagnostic assessments, and guided analysis ensure that learners strengthen fundamentals, master application, and improve accuracy.', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1.\r\nStrengthen foundational subject knowledge across core TET subjects.\r\n2.\r\nApply concepts effectively in competency-based questions.\r\n3.\r\nRecognize and avoid common mistakes that lower scores.\r\n4.\r\nImprove speed and accuracy in subject-based problem-solving.\r\n5.\r\nGain confidence in handling high-weightage sections of TET.', 'Improved conceptual clarity in Math, EVS, and Language.\r\nâ€¢\r\nAbility to solve competency-based questions with accuracy.\r\nâ€¢\r\nEnhanced problem-solving speed and confidence.\r\nâ€¢\r\nExam-readiness in subject-specific areas.', 'Subject-specific application strategies.\r\nâ€¢\r\nPersonalized feedback from diagnostic assessments.\r\nâ€¢\r\nPractice-driven mastery through TET-style drills.\r\nâ€¢\r\nClear roadmap for tackling high-weightage questions.', 'Analytical problem-solving\r\nâ€¢\r\nCompetency-based question application\r\nâ€¢\r\nError identification & correction\r\nâ€¢\r\nExam-specific subject expertise\r\nâ€¢\r\nSelf-assessment & reflective learning', 'Module 1: Diagnostic Assessment & Study Roadmap\r\nModule 2: Core Math Mastery for TET\r\nModule 3: EVS Concepts & Application\r\nModule 4: Language & Grammar Mastery\r\nModule 5: Common Mistakes & Misconceptions in TET\r\nModule 6: Practice Drills & Final Assessment', 'This course bridges the gap between subject knowledge and exam application, ensuring teachers are not just knowledgeable but also exam-ready. By the end, educators will have a personalized strategy, subject mastery, and the confidence to excel in TET.', 'uploads/brochures/FED-TET-PE-01.pdf', '2025-10-04 02:25:37'),
(2, -1, 'Ref Code: FED-TET-PE-03', ' TET Exam Strategy & Time Management', '2 weeks (6â€“8 hrs)', 'Optimize exam attempts, improve speed, and manage stress effectively', 'Live workshops, timed practice drills, self-paced strategy modules', 'Success in TET is not just about what you know, but how effectively you apply your knowledge under exam conditions.\r\nMany educators lose marks due to poor time management, question prioritization, or stress. This course provides\r\nstructured strategies and timed practice, ensuring participants can maximize their attempts, reduce anxiety, and\r\nconfidently handle the pressure of competency-based exams.', 'â€¢ Familiarity with TET syllabus and exam pattern.\r\nâ€¢ Prior attempt at mock tests or basic awareness of exam sections.\r\nâ€¢ Willingness to practice under timed conditions.\r\n', 'â€¢ Aspiring teachers preparing for CTET/TET exams.\r\nâ€¢ Educators who struggle with speed and accuracy in exams.\r\nâ€¢ Teachers seeking to refine their exam strategy and boost confidence.', 'is 2-week intensive program equips participants with proven exam strategies, time optimization techniques, and\r\nstress management tools. Through timed drills, live workshops, and guided analysis, educators learn to attempt\r\nquestions smartly, balance accuracy with speed, and handle exam pressure.', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1. Understand the TET exam blueprint and mark distribution.\r\n2. Prioritize questions strategically to maximize scores.\r\n3. Apply effective time management techniques during exams.\r\n4. Manage stress and maintain focus under exam pressure.\r\n5. Improve overall accuracy and speed through practice.\r\n', 'â€¢ Confidence in approaching the TET exam strategically.\r\nâ€¢ Ability to balance accuracy and speed during timed attempts.\r\nâ€¢ Reduced stress levels and improved exam temperament.\r\n', 'â€¢ Personalized time management plan.\r\nâ€¢ Practical prioritization techniques.\r\nâ€¢ Stress m