ms\r\nâ€¢ Stress control drills before and during practice exams\r\nObjective: Help educators stay calm and composed under pressure.\r\nOutcome: Reduced stress and improved exam resilience.\r\nKey Skills: Emotional regulation, exam mindset, confidence buildingModule 5: Practice Drills & Simulation\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Sectional timed drills\r\nâ€¢ Mixed question paper under exam conditions\r\nâ€¢ Error analysis & corrective strategies\r\nâ€¢ Peer/mentor review of performance\r\nâ€¢ Personalized strategy adjustments\r\nObjective: Apply strategies in realistic exam simulations.\r\nOutcome: Participants build exam confidence and readiness.\r\nKey Skills: Exam application, reflective improvement, strategy refinement\r\n', 'This course transforms exam preparation from random practice into structured, strategic performance. By the end,\r\neducators will not only know their subjects but also know how to maximize marks, manage time, and stay calm under\r\npressure. Theyâ€™ll walk into the exam hall with confidence, clarity, and proven strategies.\r\nDuration: 2 weeks (6â€“8 hrs)\r\nDelivery Methodology: Blended (live workshops, timed drills, reflective feedback, strategy coaching)', 'uploads/brochures/Ref_Code__FED-TET-PE-03.pdf', '2025-11-14 09:01:07'),
(3, 2, 'Ref Code: FED-TET-PE-02', 'Pedagogy Excellence & Child Development', '3 weeks (10â€“12 hrs)', 'Master learner-centered teaching methods & child development concepts aligned with NEP/NCTE', 'Video lessons, interactive case studies, group discussions, reflective tasks', 'Effective teaching requires more than subject knowledge â€” it requires understanding how learners grow, develop, and\r\nrespond to teaching methods. Many TET candidates struggle with competency-based pedagogy and child development\r\nquestions, even when they understand theory. This course ensures teachers can bridge theory with practice, master\r\nNEP/NCTE-aligned teaching strategies, and confidently answer pedagogy-based questions.\r\n', 'â€¢ Familiarity with teaching basics (formal or informal).\r\nâ€¢ Awareness of TET syllabus pedagogy & child psychology section.\r\nâ€¢ Interest in applying educational theory to classroom practice.\r\n', 'â€¢ Aspiring teachers preparing for CTET/TET.\r\nâ€¢ Educators seeking to refresh pedagogy & child development knowledge.\r\nâ€¢ Teacher trainees in B.Ed./D.El.Ed. programs.\r\n', 'his 3-week program equips educators with a deep understanding of pedagogy, learning theories, and child\r\ndevelopment while focusing on exam-relevant application. Using case studies, simulations, and practice drills,\r\neducators will develop confidence in solving competency-based pedagogy questions and applying insights to real\r\nclassrooms.\r\nOur targeted modules ensure educators can tackle pedagogy and child psychology questions with confidence and\r\naccuracy.', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1. Understand core principles of pedagogy and child development.\r\n2. Apply psychological and pedagogical theories to exam and classroom contexts.\r\n3. Analyze and solve case-based pedagogy questions.\r\n4. Interpret NEP/NCTE guidelines for teaching practices.\r\n5. Build exam confidence in pedagogy-related sections.\r\n', 'â€¢ Stronger mastery of pedagogy & child development concepts.\r\nâ€¢ Improved accuracy in answering competency-based pedagogy questions.\r\nâ€¢ Ability to adapt pedagogy to learner needs and inclusive classrooms.', 'â€¢ NEP/NCTE-aligned pedagogy framework.\r\nâ€¢ Hands-on practice with pedagogy Qs and case studies.\r\nâ€¢ Practical techniques for inclusive and reflective teaching.', 'â€¢ Pedagogical reasoning\r\nâ€¢ Application of child psychology\r\nâ€¢ Inclusive teaching strategies\r\nâ€¢ Case-based exam question solving\r\nâ€¢ NEP/NCTE framework integration', 'Module 1: Foundations of Pedagogy\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Learner-centered methods\r\nSystem Generated Document | Does Not Require Signature | asm-09/28/25\r\nâ€¢ Constructivist approaches to teaching\r\nâ€¢ Role of the teacher in 21st-century classrooms\r\nâ€¢ Pedagogical approaches as per NEP 2020\r\nâ€¢ Competency-based pedagogy question practice\r\nObjective: Build a strong foundation in pedagogy principles.\r\nOutcome: Learners understand pedagogy concepts and apply them to exam questions.\r\nKey Skills: Pedagogical reasoning, exam alignment\r\nModule 2: Child Development & Learning\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Piagetâ€™s stages of cognitive development\r\nâ€¢ Vygotskyâ€™s socio-cultural theory of learning\r\nâ€¢ Emotional and social development in children\r\nâ€¢ Learning needs and differences\r\nâ€¢ Competency-based child development question drillsObjective: Deepen understanding of child development and psychology.\r\nOutcome: Ability to confidently approach child development questions in TET.\r\nKey Skills: Psychological application, learner analysis\r\nModule 3: Inclusive & Differentiated Instruction\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Principles of inclusive education\r\nâ€¢ Teaching strategies for diverse learners\r\nâ€¢ Differentiated instruction techniques\r\nâ€¢ Classroom adaptations for various learning needs\r\nâ€¢ Case study practice on inclusion-based questions\r\nObjective: Equip teachers with inclusive and adaptable pedagogy strategies.