(4, 4, 'FED-TET-PE-04', 'Mock Tests & Performance Mastery', '4 weeks (8â€“10 hrs total, with weekly practice tests', 'Real exam practice, performance analysis, and targeted improvement', ' Online mock tests, AI/mentor feedback, peer discussions, revision planning', 'Practice is the bridge between preparation and success. Many educators study well but underperform in the actual TET\r\nexam due to lack of real exam practice, poor error analysis, and weak performance tracking. This course offers fulllength simulated TET mock tests with in-depth analysis and personalized feedback, ensuring participants can practice\r\nunder real conditions and fine-tune their strategies for maximum performance', 'â€¢ Completion of subject and pedagogy refresher courses (recommended).\r\nâ€¢ Familiarity with TET syllabus and exam structure.\r\nâ€¢ Commitment to taking tests under timed conditions', 'â€¢ Aspiring teachers preparing for TET who want real exam practice.\r\nâ€¢ Educators who need to track progress and refine weak areas.\r\nâ€¢ Teachers seeking to build exam temperament and confidence.', 'This 4-week course provides full-length TET mock tests, sectional practice, and detailed performance reviews. Each\r\nmock test replicates the actual exam environment, followed by personalized feedback and analytics. Educators will\r\nidentify their strong and weak areas, correct recurring mistakes, and refine exam strategies.Our targeted modules ensure educators can approach competency-based TET questions with confidence, accuracy,\r\nand exam-ready temperament.', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1. Attempt full-length TET papers under exam conditions.\r\n2. Analyze performance and identify strengths/weaknesses.\r\n3. Apply corrective strategies to minimize errors.\r\n4. Build exam stamina and temperament for high-stakes performance.\r\n5. Develop a personalized revision and practice plan.\r\n', 'â€¢ Familiarity with exam conditions and time limits.\r\nâ€¢ Improved accuracy through detailed error analysis.\r\nâ€¢ Strengthened weak sections through targeted practice.\r\nâ€¢ Greater confidence in handling full exam papers.', 'â€¢ Access to exam-simulated mock tests.\r\nâ€¢ Personalized performance reports.\r\nâ€¢ Clear gap analysis and action plan.\r\nâ€¢ Enhanced exam temperament and readiness.\r\n', 'â€¢ Test-taking strategy\r\nâ€¢ Performance analysis\r\nâ€¢ Error correction techniques\r\nâ€¢ Stamina and focus building\r\nâ€¢ Adaptive learning and improvement', 'Module 1: Introduction to Exam Simulation\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Importance of mock tests in preparation\r\nâ€¢ How to replicate exam conditions\r\nâ€¢ Setting up a test-taking environment\r\nâ€¢ Tracking baseline performance\r\nâ€¢ Pre-assessment mock test\r\nObjective: Familiarize learners with exam simulation.\r\nOutcome: Participants understand how to simulate exam conditions effectively.\r\nKey Skills: Exam environment readiness, baseline analysisModule 2: Sectional Mock Tests (Math, Pedagogy, Language, EVS)\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Timed sectional mock for Math\r\nâ€¢ Timed sectional mock for Language & Grammar\r\nâ€¢ Timed sectional mock for EVS\r\nâ€¢ Pedagogy-focused sectional drill\r\nâ€¢ Sectional performance review\r\nObjective: Build sectional competence.\r\nOutcome: Educators strengthen weak areas section by section.\r\nKey Skills: Sectional mastery, targeted practice\r\nModule 3: Full-Length TET Mock Test â€“ Round 1\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Full-length exam simulation\r\nâ€¢ Time management during the mock\r\nâ€¢ Self-review of attempted questions\r\nâ€¢ Mentor/AI performance analysis\r\nâ€¢ Error log creationObjective: Experience the full exam and evaluate performance.\r\nOutcome: Clear identification of strengths and weaknesses.\r\nKey Skills: Exam stamina, reflective analysis\r\nModule 4: Error Analysis & Strategy Refinement\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Categorizing errors (conceptual, careless, time-bound)\r\nâ€¢ Correcting frequent mistakes\r\nâ€¢ Adjusting strategies for question prioritization\r\nâ€¢ Revisiting weak concepts with focused practice\r\nâ€¢ Personalized feedback session\r\nObjective: Minimize recurring mistakes and refine exam strategy.\r\nOutcome: Improved accuracy and efficiency.\r\nKey Skills: Error correction, adaptive strategyModule 5: Full-Length TET Mock Test â€“ Round 2\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Second full-length practice exam\r\nâ€¢ Application of refined strategies\r\nâ€¢ Comparative analysis with first mock test\r\nâ€¢ Personalized revision roadmap\r\nâ€¢ Final confidence-building session\r\nObjective: Test readiness after strategy refinement.\r\nOutcome: Participants demonstrate growth and readiness for the actual exam.\r\nKey Skills: Final preparation, exam confidence', 'This course ensures educators are not just practicing, but practicing with purpose. Through full-length simulations, error\r\nanalysis, and personalized improvement plans, teachers build the competence, confidence, and resilience needed to\r\nexcel in the TET exam.', 'uploads/brochures/FED-TET-PE-04.pdf', '2025-11-14 10:09:28'),
(5, 5, 'Ref Code: FED-TET-PE-05', 'Confidence & Exam Readiness Bootcamp', '1 week (4â€“5 hrs', 'Build exam confidence, stress management, and readiness for high-stakes performance', 'Live interactive bootcamp, mentoring, simulations, reflective practice', 'Even well-prepared educators sometimes underperform in TET due to stress, lack of confidence, and poor exam\r\ntemperament. This bootcamp is designed to strengthen educatorsâ€™ mental and emotional resilience, giving them the\r\nconfidence and calm mindset needed to excel on exam day. Through mentoring, simulations, and targeted stress\r\nmanagement tools, teachers learn how to approach competency-based questions with composure and clarity.', 'â€¢ Prior familiarity with TET syllabus and practice (subject mastery assumed).\r\nâ€¢ Willingness to engage in reflective and experiential exercises.\r\nâ€¢ Access to a quiet space for live simulations and workshops.', 'â€¢ Aspiring teachers who feel exam stress or anxiety impacts performance.\r\nâ€¢ Educators who want to improve exam temperament and mental resilience.\r\nâ€¢ Teachers seeking personalized mentoring and final readiness preparation.', 'This 1-week bootcamp builds exam confidence and readiness through interactive mentoring, stress-management\r\npractices, and live exam simulations. Educators participate in role plays, relaxation exercises, and readiness\r\nassessments to prepare for the pressure of exam conditions.\r\nSystem Generated Document | Does Not Require Signature | asm-09/28/25\r\nOur targeted modules ensure educators can approach competency-based TET questions with the confidence,\r\ncalmness, and accuracy required to succeed.', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1. Manage exam-related stress using proven relaxation techniques.\r\n2. Strengthen their confidence and self-belief for exam success.\r\n3. Develop strategies to maintain focus and composure under pressure.\r\n4. Simulate exam-day conditions for mental readiness.\r\n5. Build a personalized confidence and stress-management plan.', 'â€¢ Reduced exam anxiety and improved calmness under pressure.\r\nâ€¢ Enhanced self-confidence and exam-day readiness.\r\nâ€¢ Ability to remain focused and composed during competency-based questions.', 'â€¢ Stress-busting toolkit for TET exam day.\r\nâ€¢ Personalized mentoring and confidence-building guidance.\r\nâ€¢ Role-play simulations to mirror exam conditions.\r\nâ€¢ Readiness assessment and final preparation plan.\r\n', 'â€¢ Stress and anxiety management\r\nâ€¢ Confidence building\r\nâ€¢ Exam temperament control\r\nâ€¢ Focus and concentration techniques\r\nâ€¢ Resilience under high-stakes conditions', 'Module 1: Building the Right Mindset\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Understanding exam anxiety and its triggers\r\nâ€¢ Importance of positive mindset in high-stakes exams\r\nâ€¢ Growth mindset principles for educators\r\nâ€¢ Reframing exam as an opportunity\r\nâ€¢ Confidence journaling exercise\r\nObjective: Establish a positive and resilient exam mindset.\r\nOutcome: Learners recognize and control negative exam thoughts.\r\nKey Skills: Growth mindset, emotional regulation\r\nModule 2: Stress Management Toolkit\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Breathing and mindfulness techniques\r\nâ€¢ Relaxation practices before and during exams\r\nâ€¢ Quick â€œresetâ€ strategies in moments of stress\r\nâ€¢ Balancing preparation with rest\r\nâ€¢ Practical exercises for daily stress relief\r\nObjective: Provide actionable tools for stress management.\r\nOutcome: Participants reduce anxiety and stay calm under exam pressure.\r\nKey Skills: Stress regulation, relaxation masteryModule 3: Confidence Building Through Simulations\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Live mock exam simulation with time pressure\r\nâ€¢ Role-play: handling exam hall scenarios\r\nâ€¢ Peer review and feedback for confidence building\r\nâ€¢ Identifying strengths and anchoring confidence in them\r\nâ€¢ Visualization exercises for success\r\nObjective: Build self-confidence through real-like practice.\r\nSystem Generated Document | Does Not Require Signature | asm-09/28/25\r\nOutcome: Educators develop calmness and confidence in simulated exam conditions.\r\nKey Skills: Exam temperament, visualization, confidence anchoringModule 4: Personalized Mentoring & Feedback\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ One-on-one mentoring sessions\r\nâ€¢ Addressing individual fears and challenges\r\nâ€¢ Building personalized readiness plans\r\nâ€¢ Peer discussion and shared strategies\r\nâ€¢ Closing confidence-boosting workshop\r\nObjective: Offer personalized strategies and mentoring support.\r\nOutcome: Teachers finish with a tailored plan for exam readiness.\r\nKey Skills: Personal resilience, individualized preparation', 'Confidence is the last-mile differentiator in clearing the TET exam. This bootcamp ensures that educators are not only\r\nacademically prepared but also mentally resilient, stress-free, and fully confident. With practical tools, mentoring, and\r\nlive simulations, teachers finish the course ready to perform at their best in the TET exam.\r\nDuration: 1 week (4â€“5 hrs)\r\nDelivery Methodology: Live interactive bootcamp, personalized mentoring, simulation-based practice', 'uploads/brochures/Ref_Code__FED-TET-PE-05.pdf', '2025-11-14 10:49:29'),
(6, 6, 'Ref Code: FED-TET-PE-06', 'Teaching Mindset & Pedagogical Adaptability', '3 weeks (8â€“10 hrs)', 'Build a growth-oriented teaching mindset and adapt pedagogy to diverse learners and modern education\r\ncontexts', ' Blended (video lessons, peer learning, reflective practice, interactive workshops)', 'Great educators are not just subject experts; they possess the right mindset and adaptability to respond to diverse\r\nlearners and evolving education policies. With NEP 2020 emphasizing flexible, student-centered teaching, many\r\neducators must learn to adapt pedagogy, embrace technology, and cultivate lifelong learning habits. This course helps\r\nteachers build the mindset and adaptability required for long-term success while preparing them to tackle competencybased pedagogy questions in TET.\r\n', 'â€¢ Basic familiarity with classroom teaching practices.\r\nâ€¢ Awareness of NEP/NCTE expectations (helpful but not mandatory).\r\nâ€¢ Openness to reflective practice and peer learning.', 'â€¢ Teachers preparing for TET and future teaching roles.\r\nâ€¢ Faculty members looking to align with NEP 2020/NCTE guidelines.\r\nâ€¢ Educators seeking to strengthen adaptability in teaching styles.\r\n', 'This 3-week course focuses on building a growth mindset, adaptability, and reflective teaching practices aligned with\r\nNEP 2020. Educators will learn strategies for differentiated instruction, technology integration, and lifelong learning.\r\n\r\n', 'By the end of this course, participants will be able to:\r\n1. Develop a growth-oriented teaching mindset.\r\n2. Adapt pedagogy to suit diverse learner needs.\r\n3. Integrate NEP-aligned approaches into teaching practice.\r\n4. Apply technology effectively in the classroom.\r\n5. Cultivate reflective and adaptive teaching habits.', 'â€¢ Ability to adjust pedagogy for varied learners and contexts.\r\nâ€¢ Improved confidence in answering competency-based pedagogy/adaptability questions.\r\nâ€¢ Lifelong learning mindset as a teacher.', 'â€¢ NEP-ready teaching strategies.\r\nâ€¢ Growth mindset framework for educators.\r\nâ€¢ Differentiated and technology-aided teaching methods.\r\nâ€¢ Practical reflective tools for continuous improvement.\r\n', 'â€¢ NEP-ready teaching strategies.\r\nâ€¢ Growth mindset framework for educators.\r\nâ€¢ Differentiated and technology-aided teaching methods.\r\nâ€¢ Practical reflective tools for continuous improvement.\r\n', 'Module 1: Developing a Growth Mindset\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Fixed vs. growth mindset in teaching\r\nâ€¢ Building resilience as an educator\r\nâ€¢ Continuous professional learning mindset\r\nâ€¢ Overcoming self-doubt and limiting beliefs\r\nâ€¢ Competency-based mindset Q practice\r\nObjective: Establish a growth mindset framework for teachers.\r\nOutcome: Educators embrace continuous learning and confidence-building.\r\nKey Skills: Resilience, mindset reframingodule 2: Pedagogical Adaptability for Diverse Learners\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Understanding diverse learning styles\r\nâ€¢ Differentiated instruction strategies\r\nâ€¢ Classroom adaptations for varied needs\r\nâ€¢ Inclusive pedagogy practices\r\nâ€¢ Case study: pedagogy adaptability questions in TET\r\nObjective: Build skills to adapt pedagogy for different learners.\r\nOutcome: Teachers effectively apply inclusive, adaptable pedagogy.\r\nKey Skills: Inclusive strategies, classroom adaptabilityodule 3: NEP 2020-Aligned Approaches\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Key NEP 2020 highlights for educators\r\nâ€¢ Competency-based and experiential learning focus\r\nâ€¢ Integrating learner-centered strategies into classrooms\r\nâ€¢ Teacher roles as facilitators of learning\r\nâ€¢ NEP-related pedagogy Q practice\r\nObjective: Equip teachers with NEP-compliant pedagogy.Outcome: Confidence in both classroom practice and exam questions.\r\nKey Skills: Policy alignment, learner-centered teachingModule 4: Technology Integration in Pedagogy\r\nSubtopics:\r\nâ€¢ Tools for digital teaching (online platforms, apps)\r\nâ€